  "body": "I'm using `Pack()` to generate a transaction that I want to sign offline, but the input arguments of my smart contract method are `bytes` greater than 32 bytes. Based on this statement: \"**arguments are all 32 bytes**\" I'm wondering if I'm trying something that its not possible.\r\n\r\nSo my question is: Is it possible to use arguments that are greater than 32 bytes with `Pack()`?\r\n\r\n```go\r\n// Pack the given method name to conform the ABI. Method call's data\r\n// will consist of method_id, args0, arg1, ... argN. Method id consists\r\n// of 4 bytes and arguments are all 32 bytes.\r\n// Method ids are created from the first 4 bytes of the hash of the\r\n// methods string signature. (signature = baz(uint32,string32))\r\nfunc (abi ABI) Pack(name string, args ...interface{}) ([]byte, error) {\r\n```",
